# Static archive of GameCon 2004 (reconstructed from the Internet Archive).
#
# The 2004 festival ran 8.-11. 7. 2004 in OLOMOUC (DDM, tř. 17. listopadu 47 +
# nearby university dorms). It was run by the Altar publishing house, and in
# 2004 GameCon was a SECTION of the whole altar.cz publisher site (path
# altar.cz/gamecon/) — the same path-era as 2005, older than the
# gamecon.altar.cz subdomain (2006-2008).
#
# Scope: the GameCon pages (~31 /gamecon/ pages, incl. the Mistrovství v DrD
# results archive vysledky95..vysledky04) served at the root, PLUS the Altar
# publisher-site nav menu it links to — the section landing pages (/altar/*,
# /arena/, /battletech/, /drd/, /drdplus/, /dech/, /hexaedr/, /akce/, /prog/,
# /odkazy/, /kontakt/, /help/, plus the altar.cz path pages /proroctvi/,
# /risesnu/) and one level deeper. All restored from web.archive.org in the 2004
# capture window (so the publisher content matches the year), transcoded
# WINDOWS-1250 -> UTF-8 (with an injected <meta charset>, since the source
# declared charset only via the HTTP header).
#
# Still out of scope (themed 404): dynamic CGI (/cgi/search.cgi, /cgi/doc/*),
# the product catalog, and links deeper than one level. (The /cgi/doc DrD rules
# tree was reconstructed only for the 2003 archive.) Assets
# (stylesheets/default.css, img/*) are served at their original absolute paths.

DirectoryIndex index.html
ErrorDocument 404 /404.html

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    RewriteEngine On

    # Serve real files / dirs directly (pages at root, assets under their paths).
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f [OR]
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # Homepage.
    RewriteRule ^$  index.html [L]

    # Everything else (cross-site Altar chrome, uncaptured) -> themed 404.
    RewriteRule ^.*$ - [R=404,L]
</IfModule>
